title: Grateful Dead Live at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium on 1993-06-25
lineage: AMS ST-250 (FOB,DFC,ORTF) > Modified Sony D10 Pro > Sony D10 Pro via Sony AES/EBU digital > Sony D8 > M-Audio Auiophile USB > Soundforge v 7.0 > CD Wave > FLAC16
description: Mississippi Half Step, Little Red Rooster, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, Althea, Cassidy, Cumberland Blues, Promised Land China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Saint Of Circumstance, Uncle John's Band-> Corinna-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text: Solid...VIVA LA RFK To my ears better than the previous aud. I was there and thought the show was "solid" Standouts included UJB, Corinna, MsHalfStep, Promised Land, Sugar Mags and The Weight. This recording captures the atmosphere at a big outdoor venue. RFK never disapppointed. Plenty of room, beer and good vibes.

my first experience..... ...and oh was it memorable.a bouncy Half-Step opened my door to Jerry. I still remember how evryonr broke into thier dance. A Rooster was next followed by other jams such as Tom Thumb`s Blues and a poppin` Althea. I have to my 1st set highlight was Cumberland Blues,the train on the big screen still vivid in my mind..they eased us out Promised Land....as we rose from the lawn,we were not disappoited. The stadium could hardly hold the energy as Jerry plucked the first few chords to China-Rider as it exploded into the mind melting jam that it is. The set rolled on ..Sugar Mag into an enchanting Wharf Rat brought us out of space and what away to end a night,but wiThe Wieght..it may have ended that show but it gave me something that night that i hold onto to this day. You know that "feeling" you got at every show,the one that you can`t describe. I felt that that night and every single show hence forth.thats how you know you came for the music.I was with them till the music stopped in 95(25+shows)that may not be a record,but we all wish we had seen one more......we miss Jerry
